    {
      "id": "664926aebadb0d1da95892449b18a76948974c74",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 269,
        "name": "Kit Westneat",
        "email": "kit.westneat@gmail.com",
        "username": "kitwestneat"
      },
      "date": "2014-12-15 21:01:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1\n\nI'd expect the test to fail if it were actually creating files on different MDTs, or really on an MDT that is not also the MGS, since the MGS is not distributing nodemaps right now. Is that a possibility in the current test framework? This will be fixed in the Milestone 3 version of nodemap, so if that's not a possibility, it's probably not worth changing the test to manually distribute the nodemaps to all the MDSes.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
